description.plain:
DJ Esco was a DJ at nightclubs when Future met Esco.

Soon after, Esco starting playing Future’s tracks in clubs like Magic City and they started collaborating.

DJ Esco was the DJ for Future’s 2014 Honest European tour.  While at the airport in Dubai Esco’s bag was searched and marijuana was found, he ended up spending “56 Nights” in a Dubai jail, which inspired Future’s 56 Nights mixtape.

Esco and Boomin they got it on smash

In an interview he said the experience was life changing and, explained To FADER:

 I came back with a plan to be the greatest, at all costs.

songs.full_title: 100it Racks by DJ ESCO (Ft. 2 Chainz, Drake & Future)
songs.title: 100it Racks

description.plain:
“100it Racks” is a braggadocious song from three of rap’s titans about their wealth. The three rappers featured on this track are worth a total of $74 million, thanks to Drake’s $60 million, Future’s $8 million and 2 Chainz’s $6 million.

This collaboration between Future and Drake adds to the long list of collaborations between the two, including their joint album What A Time To Be Alive, “Grammys,” “Where Ya At,” “Never Satisfied,” “Shit (Remix),” “Fo Real” and “Tony Montana.”

While 2 Chainz and Future have never been featured on each other’s songs, they have been frequent featured artists together, such as “3500,” and even teased the idea of a potential collaboration project.
